WILD TAPIT was three wide through the turn, came into the lane from the four path, moved to loomed a threatening third inside the eighth pole then flattened out late. TOPF ROAD RULES chased the pace from the three path into the turn, was three wide in late turn when a contender then tired. FEVER TEMPLE trailed throughout while off the inside.
